%N A391207 The smallest nonnegative integer k such that n + k is not a sum of two squares.
%C A391207 The value of a(n) is at most 3 since among 4 consecutive integers there is one congruent 3 modulo 4 and no such number is a sum of two squares.
%o A391207 (PARI) isSumOfTwoSquares(n) = { my(f=factor(n)); for(i=1, #f[, 1], if(f[i, 2] % 2 && f[i, 1] % 4 == 3, return(0))); 1 }
%o A391207 a(n) = { my(r=0); while(isSumOfTwoSquares(n+r), r=r+1); r }
